The Osun State Government on Sunday recorded two new COVID-19 cases. Dr Rafiu Isamotu, Commissioner for Health in the state, said the two new COVID-19 cases were mother and son. The new recorded cases now bring the total tally in the state to 36 with three recorded deaths. In a tweet, Isamotu disclosed that the two cases were relatives of a previously confirmed COVID-19 patient. “#Covid19Osun Update as at 3rd May, 2020: Two new cases of #COVID-19 infection confirmed today (Sunday), wife and son of a previously confirmed case. “Total confirmed cases in Osun now 36; active cases, 10; the number of deaths – 3,” Isamotu tweeted.